Overview of VIM Commands
------------------------

See .vimrc

See also
http://pascalprecht.github.io/2014/03/18/why-i-use-vim/

http://tnerual.eriogerg.free.fr/vimqrc-ge.html

Change Modes
--------------------------------------- 
i: Insert Mode
a: Insert After
v: Visuell Mode
o: INsert a New Line after Current
O: INsert a new Line BEFORE current
Esc: Normal Mode

Copy/Paste
----------
p: Paste after
P: Paste before
yy: Copy current Line

dd: Drop the Line
x: Delete Char

Undo
-----
u: Undo
Ctrl+r: Redo

Move in the Line
---------------------------------------
0: Go to the first Column
^: Go to the first non Blank Character
$: Go to the last Column
g_: Go to the last non Blank Character


Move in the Document
---------------------
H: Go to Top / High
M: Go to Middle
G: Go To Bottom

Search
------
/Suchbegriff Find the next occurence
n Find the next occurence

Siehe
https://hpv.leo.uberspace.de/wordpress/vim-6-suchen-und-ersetzen/

